        "## üöÄ Course Ground Rules: Core Principles {.center}\n",
        "\n",
        "::: {.callout-note}\n",
        "## Welcome to Digital Humanities!\n",
        "\n",
        "Please adhere to these core principles throughout the course:\n",
        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        "1. **Be Open-Minded** {.principle}\n",
        "\n",
        "   ::: {.principle-content}\n",
        "   - Approach new concepts and methods without preconceptions.\n",
        "   - Set aside any stereotypes or misconceptions about digital technologies in humanities.\n",
        "   - Remain receptive to diverse perspectives and unconventional ideas.\n",
        "   :::\n",
        "\n",
        "2. **Embrace Frustration as Progress** {.principle}\n",
        "\n",
        "   ::: {.principle-content}\n",
        "   - Understand that frustration is a normal part of the learning process.\n",
        "   - View challenges as opportunities for growth rather than obstacles.\n",
        "   - Give yourself time to work through difficult concepts or technical issues.\n",
        "   :::\n",
        "\n",
        "3. **Own Your Learning** {.principle}\n",
        "\n",
        "   ::: {.principle-content}\n",
        "   - Take responsibility for your educational journey in this course.\n",
        "   - Actively seek out resources and ask questions when you need help.\n",
        "   - Set personal learning goals and work consistently towards achieving them.\n",
        "   :::\n",
        "\n",
        "4. **Don't Fool Yourself** {.principle}\n",
        "\n",
